  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, specialized datasets for specific targets are also common, such as ⟨focal method, assertion statement⟩ pairs in the ATLAS dataset for enhancing oracle generation [144], or ⟨bug report, test case⟩ pairs from Defects4J for bug reproduction [110].",
    "However, a key challenge is that these datasets, mined from open-source projects at scale, often suffer from significant noise.",
    "Research reveals that up to 43% of the data may contain syntax errors, irrelevance between tests and code, or extremely low coverage.",
    "This observation leads to a crucial, counter-intuitive finding, \"less is more\".",
    "By filtering this noisy data through dedicated data cleaning frameworks such as CleanTest, the performance of fine-tuned models (including code coverage and defect detection capability) improves significantly even with a drastically reduced Task FormulationTo frame test generation as a learnable sequence-to-sequence Code-to-Test: Maps method source to a full test case [5,126]."
  ],
